obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5513)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. 1st December, 2007, sub-sections (1), (2), (3) and (4) of sec. 7, ss. 8, 9, 10 and 20, vide notification No. S.O. 1955(E), dated 16th November, 2007, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec 3(ii).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5513&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Cigarettes and Other`
  line `Tobacco Products (Prohibition of Advertisement and Regulation of Trade and Commerce, Production,`
  line `Supply and Distribution) Act, 2003.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5514)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Declaration as to expediency of control by the Union.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5514&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `It is hereby declared that it is expedient in`
  line `the public interest that the Union should take under its control the tobacco industry.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5515)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5515&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) advertisement includes any visible representation by way of notice, circular, label, wrapper`
  line `or other document and also includes any announcement made orally or by any means of producing or`
  line `transmitting light, sound, smoke or gas;`
  line
  line `(b) cigarette includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) any roll of tobacco wrapped in paper or in any other substance not containing tobacco,`
  line
  line `(ii) any roll of tobacco wrapped in any substance containing tobacco, which, by reason of its`
  line `appearance, the type of tobacco used in the filter, or its packaging and labelling is likely to be`
  line `offered to, or purchased by, consumers as cigarette, but does not include beedi, cheroot and cigar;`
  line
  line `(c) distribution includes distribution by way of samples, whether free or otherwise;`
  line
  line `(d) export, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means taking out of India`
  line `to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(e) foreign language means a language which is neither an Indian language nor the English`
  line language;
  line
  line `(f) import, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means bringing into India`
  line `from a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(g) Indian language means a language specified in the Eighth Schedule to the Constitution, and`
  line `includes any dialect of such language;`
  line
  line `(h) label means any written, marked, stamped, printed or graphic matter, affixed to, or`
  line `appearing upon, any package;`
  line
  line `(i) package includes a wrapper, box, carton, tin or other container;`
  line
  line `(j) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(k) production, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, includes the making of`
  line `cigarettes, cigars, cheroots, beedis, cigarette tobacco, pipe tobacco, hookah tobacco, chewing tobacco,`
  line `pan masala or any chewing material having tobacco as one of its ingredients (by whatever name`
  line `called) or snuff and shall include--`
  line
  line `(i) packing, labelling or re-labelling, of containers;`
  line
  line `(ii) re-packing from bulk packages to retail packages; and`
  line
  line `(iii) the adoption of any other method to render the tobacco product marketable;`
  line
  line `(l) public place means any place to which the public have access, whether as of right or not, and`
  line `includes auditorium, hospital buildings, railway waiting room, amusement centres, restaurants, public`
  line `offices, court buildings, educational institutions, libraries, public conveyances and the like which are`
  line `visited by general public but does not include any open space;`
  line
  line `(m) sale, with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means any transfer of`
  line `property in goods by one person to another, whether for cash or on credit, or by way of exchange, and`
  line `whether wholesale or retail, and includes an agreement for sale, and offer for sale and exposure for`
  line sale;
  line
  line `(n) smoking, means smoking of tobacco in any form whether in the form of cigarette, cigar,`
  line `beedis or otherwise with the aid of a pipe, wrapper or any other instruments;`
  line
  line `(o) specified warning means such warnings against the use of cigarettes or other tobacco`
  line `products to be printed, painted or inscribed on packages of cigarettes or other tobacco products in`
  line `such form and manner as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) tobacco products means the products specified in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act 34 of 2003.--In section 3 of the Cigarettes and Other Tabacco`
  line `Products (Prohibition of Advertisement and Regulation of Trade and Commerce, Production, Supply and`
  line `Distribution) Act, 2003 (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), after clause (e), the following`
  line `clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(ee) hookah bar means an establishment where people gather to smoke tobacco from a community`
  line `hookah or narghile which is provided individually;`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 60 of 2018, s. 2.]`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3 of Act 34 of 2003.--In the Cigarettes and Other Tobacco Products`
  line `(Prohibition of Advertisement and Regulation of Trade and Commerce, Production, Supply and`
  line `Distribution) Act, 2003 (hereinafter referred to as the principal Act), in section 3, after clause (e), the`
  line `following clause shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `(ee) hookah bar means an establishment where people gather to smoke tobacco from a communal`
  line `hookah or narghile which is provided individually;.`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 27 of 2017, s. 2.]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 3, Central Act No. 34 of 2003.-In section 3 of the Cigarettes and Other`
  line `Tobacco Products (Prohibition of Advertisement and Regulation of Trade and Commerce, Production,`
  line `Supply and Distribution) Act, 2003 (Central Act No. 34 of 2003), hereinafter referred to as the principal`
  line `Act, after the existing clause (e) and before the existing clause (f), the following clause shall be inserted,`
  line `namely:-`
  line
  line `“(ee) “hookah bar” means an establishment where people gather to smoke tobacco from a communal`
  line `hookah or narghile which is provided individually;”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 1 of 2020, s. 2.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5516)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Prohibition of smoking in a public place.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5516&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `No person shall smoke in any public place:`
  line
  line `Provided that in a hotel having thirty rooms or a restaurant having seating capacity of thirty persons`
  line `or more and in the airports, a separate provision for smoking area or space may be made.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 4A is Act 34 of 2003.In the principal Act, after section 4, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Prohibition of hookah bar.--4A.Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no person shall,`
  line `either on his own or on behalf of any other person, open or run any hookah bar in any place including the`
  line `eating house.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- The term eating house shall have the same meaning as assigned to it by clause (5A)`
  line `of section 2 of the Gujarat Police Act, 1951 (Bom. XXII of 1951)..`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 27 of 2017, s. 3.]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 4A in Act 34 of 2003.--After section 4 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Prohibition of hookab bar.--4A.Notwithstading anything contained in this Act, no person shall,`
  line `either on his own or on behalf of any other person, open or run any hookah bar in any place including the`
  line `eating house.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The term eating house shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (5A) of`
  line `section 2 of the Maharashtra Police Act (XXII of 1951)..`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 60 of 2018, s. 3.]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 4A, Central Act No. 34 of 2003.-after the existing section 4 and before the`
  line `existing section 5 of the principal Act, the following shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `“4A. Prohibition of hookah bar.-Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, no person shall,`
  line `either on his own or on behalf of any other person, open or run any hookah bar in any place including the`
  line `eating house.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-The term ‘eating house’ means any place where food or refreshment of any kind is`
  line `provided for visitors or sold for consumption therein.”.`
  line
  line `[VideRajasthan Act 1 of 2020, s. 3.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5517)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Prohibition of advertisement of cigarettes and other tobacco products.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5517&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person engaged`
  line `in, or purported to be engaged in the production, supply or distribution of cigarettes or any other tobacco`
  line `products shall advertise and no person having control over a medium shall cause to be advertised`
  line `cigarettes or any other tobacco products through that medium and no person shall take part in any`
  line `advertisement which directly or indirectly suggests or promotes the use or consumption of cigarettes or`
  line `any other tobacco products.`
  line
  line `(2) No person, for any direct or indirect pecuniary benefit, shall--`
  line
  line `(a) display, cause to display, or permit or authorise to display any advertisement of cigarettes or`
  line `any other tobacco product; or`
  line
  line `(b) sell or cause to sell, or permit or authorise to sell a film or video tape containing`
  line `advertisement of cigarettes or any other tobacco product; or`
  line
  line `(c) distribute, cause to distribute, or permit or authorise to distribute to the public any leaflet,`
  line `hand-bill or document which is or which contains an advertisement of cigarettes or any other tobacco`
  line `product; or`
  line
  line `(d) erect, exhibit, fix or retain upon or over any land, building, wall, hoarding, frame, post or`
  line `structure or upon or in any vehicle or shall display in any manner whatsoever in any place any`
  line `advertisement of cigarettes or any other tobacco product:`
  line
  line `Provided that this sub-section shall not apply in relation to--`
  line
  line `(a) an advertisement of cigarettes or any other tobacco product in or on a package containing`
  line `cigarettes or any other tobacco product;`
  line
  line `(b) advertisement of cigarettes or any other tobacco product which is displayed at the entrance or`
  line `inside a warehouse or a shop where cigarettes and any other tobacco products are offered for`
  line `distribution or sale.`
  line
  line `(3) No person, shall, under a contract or otherwise promote or agree to promote the use or`
  line `consumption of--`
  line
  line `(a) cigarettes or any other tobacco product; or`
  line
  line `(b) any trade mark or brand name of cigarettes or any other tobacco product in exchange for a`
  line `sponsorship, gift, prize or scholarship given or agreed to be given by another person.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5518)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Prohibition on sale of cigarette or other tobacco products to a person below the age of eighteen years and in particular area.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5518&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No person shall sell, offer for sale, or permit sale of, cigarette or`
  line `any other tobacco product--`
  line
  line `(a) to any person who is under eighteen years of age, and`
  line
  line `(b) in an area within a radius of one hundred yards of any educational institution.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5519)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Restrictions on trade and commerce in, and production, supply and distribution of cigarettes and other tobacco products.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 38 of 2007, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 24-9-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5519&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, directly or indirectly, produce, supply or distribute cigarettes or any other tobacco products unless every package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products`
  line `produced, supplied or distributed by him bears thereon, or on its label ^1[such specified warning including`
  line `a pictorial warning as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(2) No person shall carry on trade or commerce in cigarettes or any other tobacco products unless`
  line `every package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products sold, supplied or distributed by him bears`
  line `thereon, or on its label, the specified warning.`
  line
  line `(3) No person shall import cigarettes or any other tobacco products for distribution or supply for a`
  line `valuable consideration or for sale in India unless every package of cigarettes or any other tobacco`
  line `products so imported by him bears thereon, or on its label, the specified warning.`
  line
  line `(4) The specified warning shall appear on not less than one of the largest panels of the package in`
  line `which cigarettes or any other tobacco products have been packed for distribution, sale or supply for a`
  line `valuable consideration.`
  line
  line `(5) No person shall, directly or indirectly, produce, supply or distribute cigarettes or any other`
  line `tobacco products unless every package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products produced, supplied or`
  line `distributed by him indicates thereon, or on its label, the nicotine and tar contents on each cigarette or as`
  line `the case may be on other tobacco products along with the maximum permissible limits thereof:`
  line
  line `Provided that the nicotine and tar contents shall not exceed the maximum permissible quantity thereof`
  line `as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5520)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Manner in which specified warning shall be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5520&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The specified warning on a package of`
  line `cigarettes or any other tobacco products shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) legible and prominent;`
  line
  line `(b) conspicuous as to size and colour;`
  line
  line `(c) in such style or type of lettering as to be boldly and clearly presented in distinct contrast to`
  line `any other type, lettering or graphic material used on the package or its label and shall be printed,`
  line `painted or inscribed on the package in a colour which contrasts conspicuously with the background of`
  line `the package or its labels.`
  line
  line `(2) The manner in which a specified warning shall be printed, painted or inscribed on a package of`
  line `cigarettes or any other tobacco products shall be such as may be specified in the rules made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) Every package containing cigarettes or any other tobacco products shall be so packed as to ensure`
  line `that the specified warning appearing thereon, or on its label, is, before the package is opened, visible to`
  line `the consumer.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5521)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Language in which the specified warning shall be expressed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5521&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the language used on a`
  line `package containing cigarettes and any other tobacco products or on its label is--`
  line
  line `(a) English, the specified warning shall be expressed in the English language;`
  line
  line `(b) any Indian language or languages, the specified warning shall be expressed in such Indian`
  line `language or languages;`
  line
  line `(c) both English and one or more Indian languages, the specified warning shall be expressed in`
  line `the English language as well as in such Indian language or languages;`
  line
  line `(d) partly English and partly any Indian language or languages, the specified warning shall be`
  line `expressed in the English language as well as in such Indian language or languages;`
  line
  line `(e) any foreign language, the specified warning shall be expressed in the English language;`
  line
  line `(f) partly any foreign language and partly English or any Indian language or languages, the`
  line `specified warning shall be expressed in the English language as well as in such Indian language or`
  line languages.
  line
  line `(2) No package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products or its label shall contain any matter or`
  line `statement which is inconsistent with, or detracts from, the specified warning.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5522)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Size of letters and figures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5522&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `No specified warning or indication of nicotine and tar contents in`
  line `cigarettes and any other tobacco products shall be deemed to be in accordance with the provisions of this`
  line `Act if the height of each letter or figure, or both the used on such warning and indication is less than the`
  line `height as may be prescribed by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5523)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Testing laboratory for nicotine and tar contents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5523&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `For purposes of testing the nicotine and tar`
  line `contents in cigarettes and any other tobacco products the Central Government shall by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette grant recognition to such testing laboratory as that Government may deem necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5524)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of entry and search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5524&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any police officer, not below the rank of a sub-inspector or any`
  line `officer of State Food or Drug Administration or any other officer, holding the equivalent rank being not`
  line `below the rank of Sub-Inspector of Police, authorise side by the Central Government or by the State`
  line `Government may, if he has any reason to suspect that any provision of this Act has been, or is being,`
  line `contravened, enter and search in the manner prescribed, at any reasonable time, any factory, building,`
  line `business premises or any other place,--`
  line
  line `(a) where any trade or commerce in cigarettes or any other tobacco products is carried on or`
  line `cigarettes or any other tobacco products are produced, supplied or distributed; or`
  line
  line `(b) where any advertisement of the cigarettes or any other tobacco products has been or is being`
  line made.
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), shall apply to every search`
  line `and seizure made under this Act.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Amendment of Section 12 of Act 34 of 2003.--In the principal Act, in section 12, in sub-section`
  line `(1),`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (b), the words or shall be added at the end;`
  line
  line `(ii) after clause (b), the following clause shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `(c) where any hookas bar is being run..`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 27 of 2017, s. 4.]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Amendment of section 12 of Act 34 of 2003.--In section 12 of the principal Act, in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (b), after the word made the word ; or shall be added;`
  line
  line `(ii) after clause (b), the following clause shall be added, namely:--`
  line
  line `(c) where any hookah bar is being run..`
  line
  line `[VideMaharashtra Act 60 of 2018, s. 4.]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Amendment of section 12, Central Act No. 34 of 2003.-In the existing sub-section (1) of section 12 of the principal Act,-`
  line
  line `(i) in clause (b), for the existing punctuation mark”. “appearing at the end, the expression”; or” shall`
  line `be substituted;`
  line
  line `(ii) after the clause (b), so amended, the following shall be added, namely:-`
  line
  line `“(c) where any hookah bar is being run.”`
  line
  line `[VideRajasthan Act 1 of 2020, s. 4.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5525)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to seize.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5525&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any police officer, not below the rank of a sub-inspector or any officer of`
  line `State Food or Drug Administration or any other officer, holding the equivalent rank being not below the`
  line `rank of Sub-Inspector of Police, authorised by the Central Government or by the State Government, has`
  line `any reason to believe that,--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of any package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products, or`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of any advertisement of cigarettes or any other tobacco products,`
  line
  line `the provisions of this Act have been, or are being, contravened, he may seize such package or`
  line `advertisement material in the manner prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) No package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products or advertisement material seized under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall be retained by the officer who seized the package or advertisement`
  line `material for a period exceeding ninety days from the date of the seizure unless the approval of the District`
  line `Judge, within the local limits of whose jurisdiction such seizure was made, has been obtained for such`
  line retention.
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 13A in Act 34 of 2003.In the principal Act, after section 13, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Power to seize.--13A If any police officer, not below the rank of a Sub-Inspector, authorized by the`
  line `State Government, has reason to believe that the provisions of section 4A have been, or are being,`
  line `contravened, he may seize any material or article used as a subject or means of hookah bar..`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 27 of 2017, s. 5.]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 13A in Act 34 of 2003.--After section 13 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Power to seize.--13A.-If any police officer, not below the rank of Assistant Police Inspector,`
  line `authorized by the State Government, has reason to believe that the provisions 4A have been, or are being,`
  line `contravened, he may seize any material or article used as a subject or means of hookah bar..`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 60 of 2018, s. 5.]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 13A, Central Act No. 34 of 2003.-After the existing section 13 and before`
  line `the existing section 14 of the principal Act, the following shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `13A. Power to seize.-If any police officer, not below the rank of Sub-Inspector, authorized by the`
  line `State Government, has reason to believe that the provisions of section 4A have been, or are being,`
  line `contravened, he may seize any material or article used as a subject or means of hookah bar.”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 1 of 2020, s. 5.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5526)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Confiscation of package.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5526&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products or any`
  line `advertisement material of cigarettes or any other tobacco products, in respect of which any provision of`
  line `this Act has been or is being contravened, shall be liable to be confiscated:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where it is established to the satisfaction of the court adjudging the confiscation that`
  line `the person in whose possession, power or control any such package of cigarettes or any other tobacco`
  line `products is found is not responsible for the contravention of the provisions of this Act, the Court may, instead of making an order for the confiscation of such package, make such other order authorised by this`
  line `Act against the person guilty of the breach of the provisions of this Act as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5527)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power to give option to pay costs in lieu of confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5527&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any confiscation of any`
  line `package of cigarettes or any other tobacco products is authorised by this Act, the court adjudging it may,`
  line `subject to such conditions as may be specified in the order adjudging the confiscation, give to the owner`
  line `thereof an option to pay, in lieu of confiscation, costs which shall be equal to the value of the goods`
  line confiscated.
  line
  line `(2) On payment of the costs ordered by the court, the seized packages shall be returned to the person`
  line `from whom they were seized on condition that such person shall, before making any distribution, sale or`
  line `supply of such packages of cigarettes or other tobacco products, get the specified warning and indication`
  line `of nicotine and tar contents incorporated on each such package.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5528)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Confiscation not to interfere with other punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5528&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `No confiscation made, costs ordered to`
  line `be paid under this Act shall prevent the infliction of any punishment to which the person affected thereby`
  line `is liable under the provisions of this Act or under any other law.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5529)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Adjudication.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5529&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Any confiscation of cigarettes or any other tobacco products may be adjudged or`
  line `costs may be ordered to be paid,--`
  line
  line `(a) without any limit, by the principal civil court of original jurisdiction within the local limits of`
  line `whose jurisdiction such confiscation has been made, costs have been ordered to be paid,`
  line
  line `(b) subject to such limits as may be specified by the Central Government in this behalf, by such`
  line `other court, not below a civil court having pecuniary jurisdiction exceeding rupees five thousand, as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5530)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Giving opportunity to the owner of seized packages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5530&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) No order adjudging confiscation or`
  line `directing payment of costs shall be made unless the owner or person in possession of the package of`
  line `cigarettes or any other tobacco products has been given a notice in writing informing him of the grounds`
  line `on which it is proposed to confiscate such package, and giving him a reasonable opportunity of making a`
  line `representation in writing, within such reasonable time as may be specified in the notice, against the`
  line `confiscation mentioned therein, and, if he so desires, of being heard personally or through a representative`
  line `in the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided that, where no such notice is given within a period of ninety days from the date of the`
  line `seizure of the package of cigarettes or of any other tobacco products, such package shall be returned, after`
  line `the expiry of that period, to the owner or the person from whose possession it was seized.`
  line
  line `(2) Save as otherwise provided in sub-section (1), the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), shall, as far as may be, apply to every proceeding referred to in sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (5531)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5531&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person, aggrieved by any decision of the court adjudging a confiscation,`
  line `ordering the payment of costs, may prefer an appeal to the court to which an appeal lies from the decision`
  line `of such court.`
  line
  line `(2) The appellate court may, after giving to the appellant an opportunity of being heard, pass such`
  line `order as it thinks fit confirming, modifying or reversing the decision or order appealed against or may`
  line `send back the case with such directions as it may think fit for a fresh decision or adjudication, as the case`
  line `may be, after taking additional evidence, if necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing any fine in lieu of confiscation or confiscating of goods of greater`
  line `value shall not be made under this section unless the appellant has had an opportunity of making a`
  line `representation and, if he so desires, of being heard in person or through a representative in his defence.`
  line
  line `(3) No further appeal shall lie against the order of the court of appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (5532)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Punishment for failure to give specified warning and nicotine and tar contents.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5532&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any`
  line `person who produces or manufactures cigarettes or tobacco products, which do not contain, either on the`
  line `package or on their label, the specified warning and the nicotine and tar contents, shall in the case of first`
  line `conviction be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both, and for the second or subsequent conviction,`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to five years and with fine which may extend to`
  line `ten thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who sells or distributes cigarettes or tobacco products which do not contain either on`
  line `the package or on their label, the specified warning and the nicotine and tar contents shall in the case of`
  line `first conviction be punishable with imprisonment for a term, which may extend to one year, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both, and, for the second or subsequent conviction,`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years and with fine which may extend to three`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (5533)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Punishment for smoking in certain places.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5533&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 4`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) An offence under this section shall be compoundable and shall be tried summarily in accordance`
  line `with the procedure provided for summary trials in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 21A in Act 34 of 2003. --In the principal Act, after section 21, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Punishment for running hookas bar.21A. ---Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 4A`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three years but which shall not be less that`
  line `one year and with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees but which shall not be less than twenty`
  line `thousand rupees..`
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 27 of 2017, s. 6.]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 21A in Act 34 of 2003.--After section 21 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Punishment for running hookah bar.21A.--Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 4A,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years but which shall not be`
  line `less than one year and with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees but which shall not be less than`
  line `fifty thousand rupees..`
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 60 of 2018, s. 6.]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 21A, Central Act No. 34 of 2003.-After the existing section 21 and before`
  line `the existing section 22 of the principal Act, the following shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `“21A. Punishment for running hookah bar.-Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 4A,`
  line `Shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to three years but which shall not be`
  line `less than one year and with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees but which shall not be less than`
  line `fifty thousand rupees.”.`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 1 of 2020, s. 6.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (5534)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Punishment for advertisement of cigarettes and tobacco products.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5534&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes the`
  line `provision of section 5 shall, on conviction, be punishable--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of first conviction, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years or`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees or with both, and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of second or subsequent conviction with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to five years and with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (5535)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Forfeiture of advertisement and advertisement material.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5535&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Where any person has been`
  line `convicted under this Act for the contravention of the provision of section 5, the advertisement and the`
  line `advertisement material for cigarettes and other tobacco products may be forfeited to the Government and`
  line `such advertisement and advertisement material shall be disposed of in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line `by rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (5536)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Punishment for sale of cigarettes or any other tobacco products in certain places or to persons below the age of eighteen years.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5536&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who contravenes the provisions of section 6`
  line `shall be guilty of an offence under this Act and shall be punishable with fine which may extend to two`
  line `hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) All offences under this section shall be compoundable and shall be tried summarily in accordance`
  line `with the procedure provided for summary trials in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (5537)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Prevention, detention and place of trial of offences under sections 4 and 6.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5537&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the Central Government`
  line `or the State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, authorise one or more persons who`
  line `shall be competent to act under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the person so authorised may, if he has reasonable ground for believing that any person`
  line `has committed an offence under section 4 or section 6, may detain such person unless the accused person`
  line `furnishes his name and address, and otherwise satisfies the officer detaining him that he will duly answer`
  line `any summons or other proceedings which may be taken against him.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person detained under sub-section (1) shall forthwith be taken before Magistrate to be dealt`
  line `with according to law.`
  line
  line `(3) Any person committing an offence under section 4 or section 6 shall be tribal for such offence in`
  line `any place in which he may be or which the State Government may notify in this behalf, as well as in any`
  line `other place in which he is liable to be tried under any law for the time being in force.`
  line
  line `(4) Every notification issued under sub-sections (1) and (3) shall be published in the Official Gazette,`
  line `and a copy thereof shall be exhibited for information to the public in some conspicuous place or places as`
  line `the State Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(5) Every person authorised under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a public servant within the`
  line `meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (5538)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5538&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company,`
  line `every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to, the`
  line `company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to be`
  line `guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall be proceeded against and`
  line `punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (5539)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Offences to be bailable.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5539&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974), an offence punishable under this Act shall be bailable.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Gujarat
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 27A in Act 34 of 2003.--In the principal Act, after section 27, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Offence under section 4A to be cognizable.27A.--An offence under section 4A shall be`
  line cognizable..
  line
  line `[Vide Gujarat Act 27 of 2017, s. 7.]`
  line
  line Maharashtra
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 27A in Act 34 of 2003--After section 27 of the principal Act, the following`
  line `section shall be inserted, namely:--`
  line
  line `Offence under section 4A to be cognizable.27A.--An offence under section 4A shall be`
  line cognizable..
  line
  line `[Vide Maharashtra Act 60 of 2018, s. 7]`
  line
  line Rajasthan
  line
  line `Insertion of new section 27A, Central Act No. 34 of 2003.- After the existing section 27 and before`
  line `the existing section 28 of the principal Act, the following shall be inserted, namely:-`
  line
  line `27A. Offence under section 4A to be congnizable.- An offence under section 4A shall be cognizable..`
  line
  line `[Vide Rajasthan Act 1 of 2020, s. 7]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (5540)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Composition of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5540&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any offence committed under section 4 or section 6 may either`
  line `before or after the institution of the prosecution be compounded by such officer authorised by Central`
  line `Government or State Government and for an amount which may not exceed two hundred rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an offence has been compounded under sub-section (1), the offender, if in custody, shall be`
  line `discharged and no further proceedings shall be taken against him in respect of such offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (5541)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5541&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie`
  line `against the Central Government or any State Government or any officer of the Central Government or any`
  line `State Government for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (5542)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Power to add any tobacco products in the Schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5542&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government, after giving by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, not less than three months' notice of its intention so to do, may, by`
  line `like notification, add any other tobacco product in respect of which it is of opinion that advertisements are`
  line `to be prohibited and its production, supply and distribution is required to be regulated under this Act, and`
  line `thereupon the Schedule shall in its application to such products be deemed to be amended accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (5543)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5543&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide for all or any`
  line `of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) specify the form and manner in which warning shall be given in respect of cigarettes or other`
  line `tobacco products under clause (o) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) specify the maximum permissible nicotine and tar contents in cigarettes or other tobacco`
  line `products under the proviso to sub-section (5) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) specify the manner in which the specified warning shall be inscribed on each package of`
  line `cigarettes or other tobacco products or its label under sub-section (2) of section 8;`
  line
  line `(d) specify the height of the letter or figure or both to be used in specified warning or to indicate`
  line `the nicotine and tar contents in cigarettes or other tobacco products under section 10;`
  line
  line `(e) provide for the manner in which entry into and search of any premises is to be conducted and`
  line `the manner in which the seizure of any package of cigarettes or other tobacco products shall be made`
  line `and the manner in which seizure list shall be prepared and delivered to the person from whose`
  line `custody any package of cigarettes or other tobacco products has been seized;`
  line
  line `(f) provide for any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act and every notification made under section 30 shall be laid, as soon`
  line `as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of`
  line `thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both`
  line `Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or notification or both Houses agree that the rule or`
  line `notification should not be made, the rule or notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (5544)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Act not to apply to cigarettes of other tobacco products which are exported.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5544&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line Nothing
  line `contained in this Act shall apply to any cigarette or other tobacco products or package of cigarettes or`
  line `other tobacco products which is exported:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise the export of any package of`
  line `cigarettes or other tobacco products, not containing the specified warning and indication of nicotine and`
  line `tar contents to any country if the law in force in that country requires that the same or similar warning and`
  line `nicotine and tar contents shall be specified on each package of cigarettes or other tobacco products.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, any cigarette or other tobacco products or package of`
  line `cigarettes or other tobacco products shall be deemed to be exported before the commencement of this Act, if the necessary steps for export have already been taken notwithstanding that the actual export has not`
  line `taken place.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (5545)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289&sectionId=5545&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00020_200334_1517807327289
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Cigarettes (Regulation of Production, Supply and Distribution) Act, 1975 (49 of 1975), is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the provisions of the`
  line `aforesaid Act, shall, in so far as such thing or action is not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the provisions of this Act as if the said provisions were in force`
  line `when such thing was done or such action was taken and shall continue in force accordingly until`
  line `superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
